WEBVTT

00:04:58.533 --> 00:05:00.398
(Music ends)

00:05:00.422 --> 00:05:01.946
I call my work --

00:05:01.970 --> 00:05:02.971
(Cheers, applause)

00:05:02.995 --> 00:05:04.145
Thank you.

00:05:04.169 --> 00:05:05.837
(Cheers, applause)

00:05:05.861 --> 00:05:08.836
I call my work stage sculpture,

00:05:09.836 --> 00:05:14.028
but of course what's really being sculpted
is the experience of the audience,

00:05:14.052 --> 00:05:16.329
and as directors and designers,

00:05:16.353 --> 00:05:17.805
we have to take responsibility

00:05:17.829 --> 00:05:20.472
for every minute
that the audience spend with us.

00:05:21.045 --> 00:05:23.263
We're a bit like pilots

00:05:23.287 --> 00:05:27.548
navigating a flight path
for a hundred thousand passengers.

00:05:28.413 --> 00:05:32.010
And in the case of the Canadian
artist The Weeknd,